# Unrestricted execve: fires on EVERY process start (including all daemon activity),
# no auid filter. f3 §3.5: unrestricted -S execve is the HIGH-volume reference.
# Adversarial contrast with rocky9-execve-auid (#4): removing the auid narrowing
# must raise the tier MEDIUM -> HIGH.
-a always,exit -S execve -k execve
